main event: Two objects were seen traveling from northeast to southwest at a high altitude over Terre Haute, Indiana on August 13, 1960.
interesting points: The objects crossed about 40-45 degrees of arc in 1 minute and 43 seconds.
The lights on the objects were white and stayed the same distance behind each other.
The witness observed the objects through binoculars and a theodolite.
The objects appeared to be between second and third magnitude brightness.
The objects dimmed in brightness as they got farther away.
sighted object: two high-altitude objects with white lights
